ndfa (0.0.0-2)

A (non)-definate finite state automaton interpreter language.

Usage: ndfa <automaton.nfa> <?args>

Args:
    --help (-h)                     - Prints this help document.
    --license                       - Prints the software license.
    --debug                         - Enabled debug messages.
    --version                       - Prints the software version.
    -i <file>                       - Specify input file.
    --string (-S) <string>          - Specify string to interpret (DFA).
    --dump-ast                      - Dumps the abstract syntax tree of the
                                    parsed program.
    --quiet (-q)                    - Supress less-important messages.
    --Quiet (-qq)                   - Supress all non-critical messages.
    --pretty-print (-pp) <file>     - Pretty-print the specified program to
                                    a file.
    --load-json (-J) <file>         - Loads a JSON representation of an automata.
                                    Expects format from: https://madebyevan.com/fsm/.
    --start <state>                 - Specify a starting state by name.
    --term-on-accept (-Toa)         - Terminate the program when any accepting
                                    state reached.
    --force-mode <NFA|DFA>          - Override the specified mode in the given
                                    program.
    --max-steps (-Max) <int>        - Specify the maximum allowed steps for the
                                    program. (Default 100).
    --auto-insert-nulls (-Ain)      - Auto insert nullstate transitions when
                                    transform not specified (DFA only).
    --build-info                    - Prints build information.